      <head>Waidhofen an der Thaya</head>
      <div>

        <p>Town in the northern part of Lower Austria [Nieder&#xF6;sterreich], 18 km (11 miles)
          from the Moravian (Czech) border. It is situated 12 km (c. 8 miles) from <ref
            cRef="kautzen">Kautzen</ref>, where <ref cRef="schenker_wilhelm">Wilhelm Schenker</ref>
            and his family lived, and 100 km (c. 60 miles) north-west of Vienna.</p>
        
        <p>Schenker's mother, <ref cRef="schenker_julia">Julia Schenker</ref>, was buried inthe
          Jewish cemetery there. A Jewish religious community [Kultusgemeinde] existed in Waidhofen,
          and is referred to in Schenker's diaries.</p>
      </div>
